 build and publish steps.\n  Line 95: │  │ agent_metadata   │  │    Dockerfile     │                           │\n  Line 166:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n  Line 182: | `--port` | - | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n  Line 245:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile if needed.\"\"\"\n  Line 248:         \"\"\"Generate Python-specific Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n  Line 251:         \"\"\"Generate Java-specific Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n  Line 282:     # Step 6: Generate Dockerfile\n  Line 421:         \"\"\"Build Docker image from Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n  Line 439: ### 6.3 Dockerfile Generation\n  Line 441: #### Python Dockerfile Template\n  Line 458: #### Java Dockerfile Template\n  Line 585:         \"\"\"Test Python Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n  Line 588:         \"\"\"Test Java Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n  Line 707: | AC004 | Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java) | Integration test: Dockerfile created |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 18: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n  Line 104: ### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n  Line 106: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n  Line 108: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n  Line 110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n  Line 112: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n  Line 113: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n  Line 115: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n  Line 117: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n  Line 119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n  Line 120: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n  Line 122: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n  Line 124: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n  Line 126: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n  Line 127: - **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n  Line 269: - [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 130 matches (30 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":130,"truncated":true},"title":"Dockerfile","time":{"start":1775874744259,"end":1775874744274}}}}
