{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874809275,"sessionID":"ses_285a01fbaffekE7jGOeMruHisg","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6317fa001iAMJAvUg5EgNOc","messageID":"msg_d7a630c7a001XVJ3bciztwCAep","sessionID":"ses_285a01fbaffekE7jGOeMruHisg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_aa70d7ce73f546ceb53bee4f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement comprehensive RBAC configuration for AgentCube, defining ServiceAccounts, Roles, and RoleBindings to enable secure, least-privilege access control for agent pods and controllers across namespaces.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: AgentCube requires proper RBAC configuration to secure communication between its components. The current Helm chart includes basic ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding, but lacks:\n12: - Namespace-scoped Roles for agents\n13: - Dedicated ServiceAccounts for agents and controllers\n14: - Granular permissions per component type\n15: \n16: The delta-spec AR-031 defines specific acceptance scenarios that need implementation.\n17: \n18: ### Goal\n19: \n20: Create RBAC manifests under `manifests/rbac/` that:\n21: - Define `agentcube-agent` ServiceAccount for agent pods\n22: - Define `agentcube-controller` ServiceAccount for control plane\n23: - Create namespace-scoped Roles with least-privilege permissions\n24: - Create ClusterRole for controller with full reconciliation access\n25: - Bind ServiceAccounts to appropriate Roles\n26: \n27: ### Value\n28: \n29: - **Security**: Follows Kubernetes RBAC best practices with least-privilege\n30: - **Isolation**: Namespace-scoped agent roles vs cluster-scoped controller roles\n31: - **Maintainability**: Clear separation of concerns between agent and controller\n32: - **Compliance**: Meets enterprise security requirements for multi-tenant access\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Scope\n37: \n38: ### In-Scope\n39: \n40: | Component | Path | Description |\n41: |-----------|------|-------------|\n42: | Agent ServiceAccount | `manifests/rbac/agent-serviceaccount.yaml` | `agentcube-agent` SA with optional imagePullSecrets |\n43: | Controller ServiceAccount | `manifests/rbac/controller-serviceaccount.yaml` | `agentcube-controller` SA in agentcube-system |\n44: | Agent Runtime Role | `manifests/rbac/agent-runtime-role.yaml` | Namespace Role for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs |\n45: | Agent Namespace Role | `manifests/rbac/agent-namespace-role.yaml` | Namespace Role for ConfigMaps, Secrets, Events |\n46: | Controller ClusterRole | `manifests/rbac/controller-clusterrole.yaml` | ClusterRole for full CRD reconciliation |\n47: | Agent Runtime RoleBinding | `manifests/rbac/agent-runtime-rolebinding.yaml` | Binds agent SA to runtime Role |\n48: | Agent Namespace RoleBinding | `manifests/rbac/agent-namespace-rolebinding.yaml` | Binds agent SA to namespace Role |\n49: | Controller RoleBinding | `manifests/rbac/controller-rolebinding.yaml` | Binds controller SA to ClusterRole |\n50: \n51: ### Out-of-Scope\n52: \n53: - RBAC for existing Helm chart templates (already exists)\n54: - Integration with external identity providers (OIDC, LDAP)\n55: - Pod security policies / Pod security standards\n56: - Network policies\n57: - Mutating/admission webhooks\n58: - Multi-cluster RBAC synchronization\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## Impact Analysis\n63: \n64: ### Dependencies\n65: \n66: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n67: |------------|---------|--------|\n68: | Kubernetes 1.19+ | RBAC API versions | Required |\n69: | AgentRuntime CRD | CRD for agent runtime management | Required |\n70: | CodeInterpreter CRD | CRD for code interpreter management | Required |\n71: | agentcube-system namespace | Controller namespace | Required |\n72: \n73: ### Upstream\n74: \n75: - `design.md` — AgentCube architecture design\n76: - `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md` — Acceptance scenarios\n77: - `manifests/agentcube/templates/rbac/` — Existing RBAC templates (AR-030)\n78: \n79: ### Downstream Consumers\n80: \n81: 1. **Agent pods** — Use agentcube-agent SA for RBAC\n82: 2. **Controller pods** — Use agentcube-controller SA\n83: 3. **Helm chart** — May reference or include these RBAC manifests\n84: 4. **Documentation** — Reference RBAC configuration for operators\n85: \n86: ### Risks\n87: \n88: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n89: |------|----------|------------|\n90: | Permission too broad | High | Follow least-privilege; separate agent vs controller roles |\n91: | Missing CRD permissions | Medium | Verify CRD API groups match deployed resources |\n92: | Namespace mismatch | Medium | Document required namespaces; add validation |\n93: | Upgrade path | Low | Document migration from AR-030 RBAC |\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Alternatives Considered\n98: \n99: ### Option 1: Use only ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding (Not Selected)\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 239. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement comprehensive RBAC configuration for AgentCube, defining ServiceAccounts, Roles, and RoleBindings to enable secure, least-privilege access control for agent pods and controllers across namespaces.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube requires proper RBAC configuration to secure communication between its components. The current Helm chart includes basic ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding, but lacks:\n- Namespace-scoped Roles for agents\n- Dedicated ServiceAccounts for agents and controllers\n- Granular permissions per component type\n\nThe delta-spec AR-031 defines specific acceptance scenarios that need implementation.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate RBAC manifests under `manifests/rbac/` that:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775874809266,"end":1775874809273}}}}
