{"type":"text","timestamp":1775874815217,"sessionID":"ses_285a01fbaffekE7jGOeMruHisg","part":{"id":"prt_d7a633281001gPG8CltfSKCyeH","messageID":"msg_d7a631df9001BPeqQIzXE90xHK","sessionID":"ses_285a01fbaffekE7jGOeMruHisg","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context. I'll create the proposal for AR-032 - Dockerfile multi-stage build to consolidate into 3 images.","time":{"start":1775874815215,"end":1775874815215}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874852533,"sessionID":"ses_285a01fbaffekE7jGOeMruHisg","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6334f1001d9EK7a0PC4iWm6","messageID":"msg_d7a631df9001BPeqQIzXE90xHK","sessionID":"ses_285a01fbaffekE7jGOeMruHisg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_18552fbcc49b4822890a4d18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, consolidating from multiple separate Dockerfiles into 3 optimized container images: `agentcube-router`, `agentcube-workload-manager`, and `agentcube-agentd` (with `picod` sidecar option).\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube currently lacks a unified Docker build strategy for its server-side Go binaries. The project has 4 binaries that need to be containerized:\n- `router` — HTTP traffic router with session management\n- `workload-manager` — Sandbox orchestration controller\n- `agentd` — Idle cleanup controller\n- `picod` — Daemon for sandbox pods (sidecar pattern)\n\nWithout multi-stage builds, each component requires separate build contexts, large base images, and manual artifact management. This increases CI/CD complexity and image size.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate consolidated Dockerfiles using multi-stage builds at `docker/`:\n- Consolidate build artifacts into minimal runtime images\n- Reduce image size by ~60-70% compared to single-stage builds\n- Use distroless or Alpine base images for production\n- Support both development (with debugging tools) and production builds\n\n### Value\n\n- **Image Size**: Smaller images (~50-100MB vs ~300MB+)\n- **Security**: Fewer packages in runtime image = smaller attack surface\n- **Build Speed**: Cached build stages speed up CI/CD\n- **Maintainability**: Single Dockerfile pattern per image type\n- **Consistency**: Unified build pipeline across all components\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Router Dockerfile | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for router binary |\n| Workload Manager Dockerfile | `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager` | Multi-stage build for workload-manager binary |\n| Agentd Dockerfile | `docker/Dockerfile.agentd` | Multi-stage build for agentd binary (includes picod option) |\n| Base build stage | `docker/base.Dockerfile` | Shared Go build environment |\n| Makefile targets | `Makefile` | Build commands for all images |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Agent workspace Dockerfiles (already exists in `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n- Helm chart image references (covered by AR-030)\n- Multi-arch image manifests (amd64/arm64)\n- Image registry push pipeline\n- Local development docker-compose setup\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| Go 1.24+ | Build toolchain for server binaries | Already in go.mod |\n| Docker/Make | Image build execution | Required |\n| Alpine Linux | Runtime base image | Required |\n| distroless/static | Optional minimal base | Optional |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- `cmd/router/` — Router source code\n- `cmd/workload-manager/` — Workload Manager source code\n- `cmd/agentd/` — Agentd source code\n- `cmd/picod/` — Picod source code\n- `go.mod` / `go.sum` — Go dependencies\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **CI/CD pipelines** — Build and push images to registry\n2. **Helm chart (AR-030)** — References image tags\n3. **E2E tests** — Deploy images to test cluster\n4. **Operators** — Pull images for production deployment\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Build cache invalidation | Medium | Structure stages to maximize cache reuse |\n| Binary size regression | Medium | Add size checks in Makefile |\n| Missing build args | Low | Document required --build-arg values |\n| Cross-platform builds | Low | Use --platform for multi-arch support |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Single monolithic image (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Simple single image to manage\n**Cons**: Bloated image, all components run even if unused, security risk, slower deployments\n\n### Option 2: Separate Dockerfiles per binary (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Maximum flexibility, no shared stages\n**Cons**: Duplicated build logic, harder to maintain, no cache sharing\n\n### Option 3: Multi-stage with shared build stage (Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Optimized image size, shared Go toolchain cache, maintainable, follows best practices\n**Cons**: More complex initial setup, requires understanding of multi-stage builds\n\n### Option 4: Distroless images (Not Selected for initial)\n\n**Pros**: Minimal possible size, highest security\n**Cons**: Debugging difficult, requires additional tooling for production support\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Image Structure\n\n```\ndocker/\n├── base.Dockerfile          # Shared Go build stage (builder)\n├── Dockerfile.router        # Router: builder → alpine runtime\n├── Dockerfile.workload-manager  # Workload Manager: builder → alpine runtime\n└── Dockerfile.agentd        # Agentd + Picod: builder → alpine runtime\n```\n\n### Build Stage Pattern\n\nEach runtime Dockerfile follows this pattern:\n\n```dockerfile\n# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /build\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /bin/[binary] ./cmd/[binary]\n\n# Stage 2: Runtime\nFROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\nRUN adduser -D -u 1000 agentcube\nUSER 1000\nCOPY --from=builder /bin/[binary] /usr/local/bin/\nENTRYPOINT [\"/usr/local/bin/[binary]\"]\n```\n\n### Image Targets\n\n| Image | Binary | Base Image | Expected Size |\n|-------|--------|------------|---------------|\n| agentcube-router | router | alpine:3.19 | ~25-30MB |\n| agentcube-workload-manager | workload-manager | alpine:3.19 | ~30-35MB |\n| agentcube-agentd | agentd + picod | alpine:3.19 | ~35-40MB |\n\n### Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n.PHONY: docker-build docker-push docker-buildx\n\ndocker-build: docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n\ndocker-build-router:\n\tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:latest .\n\ndocker-build-workload-manager:\n\tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:latest .\n\ndocker-build-agentd:\n\tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:latest .\n\ndocker-push: docker-build\n\tdocker push agentcube-router:latest\n\tdocker push agentcube-workload-manager:latest\n\tdocker push agentcube-agentd:latest\n```\n\n### Build Args\n\n| Arg | Default | Purpose |\n|-----|---------|---------|\n| GO_VERSION | 1.24 | Go toolchain version |\n| BUILDER_IMAGE | golang:1.24-alpine | Build stage base |\n| RUNTIME_IMAGE | alpine:3.19 | Runtime stage base |\n| BINARY_VERSION | dev | Binary version info |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Create directory structure\n\n- [ ] Create `docker/` directory\n- [ ] Create `docker/base.Dockerfile` for shared Go build environment\n\n### Phase 2: Implement Router Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] Create `docker/Dockerfile.router` with multi-stage build\n- [ ] Add health check endpoint configuration\n- [ ] Test build locally\n\n### Phase 3: Implement Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] Create `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager`\n- [ ] Configure Redis connection via env vars\n- [ ] Test build locally\n\n### Phase 4: Implement Agentd Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] Create `docker/Dockerfile.agentd`\n- [ ] Include picod as secondary binary or sidecar\n- [ ] Test build locally\n\n### Phase 5: Add Makefile targets\n\n- [ ] Add `docker-build-*` targets to Makefile\n- [ ] Add `docker-push` target\n- [ ] Add size validation target\n\n### Phase 6: CI integration\n\n- [ ] Add GitHub Actions workflow for docker build/push\n- [ ] Add image size checks to CI\n- [ ] Configure buildx for multi-arch (future)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| DOCKER-001 | Build router image | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router` succeeds, image ~25-30MB |\n| DOCKER-002 | Build workload-manager image | Image builds successfully, ~30-35MB |\n| DOCKER-003 | Build agentd image | Image builds successfully, includes agentd and picod, ~35-40MB |\n| DOCKER-004 | Verify binary executes | `docker run --rm agentcube-router version` outputs version |\n| DOCKER-005 | Verify non-root user | Running container uses non-root UID (1000) |\n| DOCKER-006 | Multi-stage layers present | `docker history` shows builder and runtime stages |\n| DOCKER-007 | Makefile targets work | `make docker-build` builds all 3 images |\n| DOCKER-008 | Cache reuse | Rebuild with no code changes uses cached stages |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Directory structure | 30 minutes |\n| Router Dockerfile | 1 hour |\n| Workload Manager Dockerfile | 1 hour |\n| Agentd Dockerfile | 1 hour |\n| Makefile integration | 30 minutes |\n| CI integration | 1 hour |\n| Testing & validation | 1 hour |\n| **Total** | **6 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to Other ARs\n\n- **AR-030** — Helm chart references these images; update values.yaml after image naming finalized\n- **AR-031** — RBAC manifests need to reference ServiceAccount names used in images\n- **AR-024** — DockerService.build_image() used for agent workspace builds, not affected","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775874852520,"end":1775874852530}}}}
